The European Banking Authority
published draft rules on how banks should calculate whether they
meeting international rules limiting the amount of business they
can do with any single company.  The  measures  update existing EU guidance, and would toughen
the rules for banks take securitizations into account when
measuring whether they are within the rules, the EBA said in a
statement on its website.  To contact the reporter on this story:
